This paper examines the effectiveness of comment removal as a moderation strategy in an online community, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also utilizes data analysis techniques, such as interrupted time-series analysis and delayed feedback approach, which are commonly used in cybernetics (cs.CY), statistical analysis and machine learning (cs.SD), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential limits of content removal as a moderation strategy, which could be relevant to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
